1843, The Economist’s sister magazine, is looking for a digital editor to cover maternity leave and work full time in our London office. This is an exciting opportunity to work at The Economist and to manage and develop its online editorial content. We are looking for a dedicated journalist, and rigorous, experienced copy-editor to help 1843 develop its online editorial strategy as well as manage the online publication schedule. You will be responsible for commissioning and editing articles, managing the title’s social-media accounts and producing weekly newsletters. You will work closely with the whole 1843 team, including the deputy digital editor, as well as The Economist’s digital news team and design team. You will be an excellent editor with great attention to detail, with ideas about how to present material visually. Experience of working with an online CMS system is preferred.  To apply, please send a cover letter, CV, three ideas for stories that we could run on 1843magazine.com and a critique of the website to 1843magazine@economist.com by August 6th. The Economist Group values diversity. We are committed to equal opportunities and creating an inclusive environment for all our employees. We welcome applicants regardless of ethnic origin, national origin, gender, race, colour, religious beliefs, disability, sexual orientation or age.